``markdown\n334: ## Individual Screen Scores\n335: \n336: | Screen | Layout | Spacing | Typography | Colors | Effects | Components | Overall |\n337: |--------|--------|---------|------------|--------|---------|------------|---------|\n338: | Dashboard | 80% | 62.5% | 100% | 87.5% | 80% | 83.3% | 81.9% |\n339: | Login | 100% | 95% | 100% | 90% | 100% | 100% | 96.2% |\n340: | Settings | 75% | 80% | 85% | 95% | 90% | 80% | 82.5% |\n341: | Profile | 90% | 85% | 95% | 100% | 85% | 90% | 90.8% |\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ### Step 2: Calculate Project-Wide Fidelity\n345: \n346: **Simple Average Method** (equal weight per screen):\n347: ```\n348: Project Fidelity = sum(screen_scores) / total_screens\n349: \n350: Example: (81.9 + 96.2 + 82.5 + 90.8) / 4 = 87.9%\n351: ```\n352: \n353: **Weighted Average Method** (weight by complexity/importance):\n354: ```markdown\n355: | Screen | Fidelity | Weight | Weighted Score |\n356: |--------|----------|--------|----------------|\n357: | Dashboard | 81.9% | 30% | 24.57% |\n358: | Login | 96.2% | 20% | 19.24% |\n359: | Settings | 82.5% | 25% | 20.63% |\n360: | Profile | 90.8% | 25% | 22.70% |\n361: \n362: Project Fidelity: 87.1%\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ### Step 3: Category Breakdown (Project-Wide)\n366: \n367: ```markdown\n368: ## Project-Wide Category Scores\n369: \n370: | Category | Average | Lowest Screen | Highest Screen |\n371: |----------|---------|---------------|----------------|\n372: | Layout | 86.3% | Settings (75%) | Login (100%) |\n373: | Spacing | 80.6% | Dashboard (62.5%) | Login (95%) |\n374: | Typography | 95.0% | Settings (85%) | Dashboard (100%) |\n375: | Colors | 93.1% | Dashboard (87.5%) | Profile (100%) |\n376: | Visual Effects | 88.8% | Dashboard (80%) | Login (100%) |\n377: | Components | 88.3% | Settings (80%) | Login (100%) |\n378: \n379: **Weakest Category**: Spacing (80.6%) - Priority for fixes\n380: **Strongest Category**: Typography (95.0%)\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ### Step 4: Generate All-Pages Report\n384: \n385: ```markdown\n386: # Design QA Report - All Pages Summary\n387: \n388: **Project**: {project-name}\n389: **Date**: {date}\n390: **Total Screens**: {count}\n391: \n392: ## Project-Wide Fidelity\n393: \n394: | Metric | Score | Rating |\n395: |--------|-------|--------|\n396: | **Overall Fidelity** | 87.9% | Minor Issues |\n397: | Highest Screen | Login (96.2%) | Pixel Perfect |\n398: | Lowest Screen | Dashboard (81.9%) | Needs Work |\n399: \n400: ## Rating Distribution\n401: \n402: | Rating | Count | Percentage |\n403: |--------|-------|------------|\n404: | Pixel Perfect (95-100%) | 1 | 25% |\n405: | Minor Issues (85-94%) | 1 | 25% |\n406: | Needs Work (70-84%) | 2 | 50% |\n407: | Major Revision (<70%) | 0 | 0% |\n408: \n409: ## Category Health\n410: \n411: | Category | Project Avg | Status | Action |\n412: |----------|-------------|--------|--------|\n413: | Layout | 86.3% | PASS | - |\n414: | Spacing | 80.6% | FAIL | Priority fixes needed |\n415: | Typography | 95.0% | PASS | - |\n416: | Colors | 93.1% | PASS | - |\n417: | Visual Effects | 88.8% | PASS | - |\n418: | Components | 88.3% | PASS | - |\n419: \n420: ## Priority Fix Queue (All Screens)\n421: \n422: | Priority | Screen | Fix | Impact |\n423: |----------|--------|-----|--------|\n424: | Critical | Dashboard | Container spacing | +2.5% |\n425: | Critical | Settings | Layout alignment | +2.0% |\n426: | High | Dashboard | Gap values | +1.5% |\n427: | High | Settings | Component padding | +1.2% |\n428: \n429: **Estimated Post-Fix Project Fidelity**: 94.5%\n430: \n431: ## Screen-by-Screen Summary\n432: \n433: | Screen | Route | Fidelity | Rating | Fixes Needed |\n434: |--------|-------|----------|--------|--------------|\n435: | Dashboard | /dashboard | 81.9% | Needs Work | 6 |\n436: | Login | /login | 96.2% | Pixel Perfect | 1 |\n437: | Settings | /settings | 82.5% | Needs Work | 5 |\n438: | Profile | /profile | 90.8% | Minor Issues | 3 |\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### All-Pages QA Command\n442: \n443: When user requests \"QA all pages\" or \"full project QA\":\n444: \n445: 1. **Scan HTML Prototypes**:\n446:    ```bash\n447:    ls html/{project}/*.html\n448:    ```\n449: \n450: 2. **Match to Implementations**:\n451:    Cross-reference with status file to find corresponding React files.\n452: \n453: 3. **Batch Process**:\n454:    For each HTML/React pair, run full fidelity calculation.\n455: \n456: 4. **Aggregate Results**:\n457:    Calculate project-wide scores using formulas above.\n458: \n459: 5. **Generate Consolidated Report**:\n460:    Single report with all screens and project summary\n461: \n462: ---\n463: \n464: ## Common Discrepancy Patterns\n465: \n466: ### Spacing (High Impact: ~2.5% each)\n467: | HTML | Common Mistake |\n468: |------|----------------|\n469: | `p-6` | `p-4` |\n470: | `gap-4` | `gap-2` |\n471: \n472: ### Typography (Medium Impact: ~1.7% each)\n473: | HTML | Common Mistake |\n474: |------|----------------|\n475: | `text-2xl` | `text-xl` |\n476: | `font-semibold` | `font-medium` |\n477: \n478: ### Colors (Medium Impact: ~1.9% each)\n479: | HTML | Common Mistake |\n480: |------|----------------|\n481: | `bg-blue-600` | `bg-blue-500` |\n482: | `bg-gray-50` | `bg-gray-100` |\n483: \n484: ### Visual Effects (Low Impact: ~1.0% each)\n485: | HTML | Common Mistake |\n486: |------|----------------|\n487: | `rounded-lg` | `rounded-md` |\n488: | `shadow-sm` | `shadow` |\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## Status File Integration\n493: \n494: Update `SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` after QA:\n495: \n496: ```markdown\n497: | Screen | Route | Status | Fidelity | Last QA |\n498: | Dashboard | /dashboard | In Progress | 81.9% (Needs Work) | 2024-01-15 |\n499: | Login | /login | Complete | 96.2% (Pixel Perfect) | 2024-01-15 |\n500: ```\n501: \n502: ---\n503: \n504: ## QA Session Checklist\n505: \n506: - [ ] HTML prototype file read\n507: - [ ] Classes extracted and categorized\n508: - [ ] React implementation file read\n509: - [ ] React classes extracted and categorized\n510: - [ ] Category scores calculated\n511: - [ ] Overall fidelity score calculated\n512: - [ ] Discrepancies listed with line numbers\n513: - [ ] Fixes generated with priority and impact\n514: - [ ] Post-fix fidelity estimated\n515: - [ ] Status file updated\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## See Also\n520: \n521: - [Design QA (Figma)](./design-qa-figma.md)\n522: - [HTML to React Converter](../convert-html-to-react.md)\n\n(End of file - total 522 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nskill_name: design-qa-html\napplies_to_local_project_only: true\nauto_trigger_regex: [design qa, design-qa, pixel-perfect, qa report, visual comparison, html qa, html prototype, fidelity score, fidelity check]\ntags: [qa, design-qa, html, pixel-perfect, fidelity]\nrelated_skills: [html-to-react-converter, design-qa-figma]\ndescription: Design QA skill for verifying React implementations against HTML prototypes. Calculates fidelity scores (0-100%) per screen and suggests prioritized fixes.\n---\n\n# Design QA Guide (HTML) with Fidelity Scoring\n\nVerify implemented React screens against HTML prototypes with quantitative fidelity scoring.\n\n> **HTML Prototypes**: Static HTML files serve as the source of truth for visual design.\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ MANDATORY ARTIFACT OUTPUT (Gate Contract)\n\n**This skill MUST write `{TARGET_DIR}/.claude-project/status/{project}/DESIGN_FIDELITY_REPORT.md`** every time it runs. The Phase 6 `frontend-gate.sh` parses this file — if it is missing or contains placeholder text, the gate FAILS. This enforces that the skill cannot be silently skipped.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/skills/qa/design-qa-html.md","time":{"start":1779193597538,"end":1779193597839}},"id":"prt_e4033c908001cjevS7XWRxoeud","sessionID":"ses_1bfcc70a6ffex3kg6yTH4x6k1U","messageID":"msg_e4033954c001eED9VeWbRpQNBI"}}
